<item>
            <title>[DERBY-5145] Provide option to limit compatibility test to combinations that include trunk</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-5145</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The compatibility test by default tests all possible client/server combinations. This includes testing already released versions against each other, like 10.6.2.1 client against 10.1.2.1 server. Testing for incompatibilities between already released versions isn&apos;t of much interest for the ongoing development. For example, when testing a change on trunk, you&apos;re really only interested in the combinations that have trunk either on the server side or on the client side. If we could filter out the combinations that didn&apos;t test any code on trunk (or some other branch we want to test), the time to run the tests could be significantly reduced.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="12502047">DERBY-5145</key>
